description:
&lt;p&gt;The Blood Sciences Department at the Wirral University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust currently has vacancies for Healthcare Science Support Workers (HSSW) – Band 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role includes working as part of a team of other staff within the Blood Sciences specimen reception.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally, you will already have experience of working within an NHS laboratory as a HSSW, but this is not essential as training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will include working within the HSSW team and you will be rostered into the laboratory departments/ sections as required. In addition you will also work at the Clatterbridge laboratory on rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is important that you have the ability to work flexibly between the hours of 07:00 and 21:00, inclusive of Saturday and Sunday, on rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are forward thinking and are always looking to improve the service we provide. This creates an ideal environment for staff to have developmental opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSusan LeeAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Lee&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email Address: susan.lee21@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
